[[塞萨洛尼基|塞萨洛尼基]]的'''古罗马广场'''（Roman Forum）位于[[亚里士多德广场|亚里士多德广场]]，设有两层柱廊，<ref name="Frommer's Greece Forum 1">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=t5Gdko3i7BYC&pg=PA611&dq=thessaloniki+forum&hl=en&ei=wFbdTtejEMqGsgaM372zBA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=8&ved=0CFkQ6AEwBw#v=onepage&q=thessaloniki%20forum&f=false|title=Frommer's Greece|author1=John S. Bowman|author2=Sherry Marker|author3=Peter Kerasiotis|author4=Rebecca Tobin|date=2008-01-25|publisher=Frommer's|accessdate=2011-12-05|archive-date=2017-02-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170214191233/https://books.google.com/books?id=t5Gdko3i7BYC&pg=PA611&dq=thessaloniki+forum&hl=en&ei=wFbdTtejEMqGsgaM372zBA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=8&ved=0CFkQ6AEwBw#v=onepage&q=thessaloniki%20forum&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref> 在20世纪60年代意外挖出。广场上有两个罗马浴场，<ref name="A Companion 1">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QsJ183uUDkMC&pg=PT275&dq=thessaloniki+forum&hl=en&ei=4FTdTqnmIM_Nsga16ZSMBA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=thessaloniki%20forum&f=false|title=A Companion to Ancient Macedonia|author1=Joseph Roisman|author2=Ian Worthington|year=2011|publisher=Wiley-Backwell|accessdate=2011-12-05|archive-date=2017-02-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170215023555/https://books.google.com/books?id=QsJ183uUDkMC&pg=PT275&dq=thessaloniki+forum&hl=en&ei=4FTdTqnmIM_Nsga16ZSMBA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=thessaloniki%20forum&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref> 其中一个已经挖掘出来，而另一个还埋在地下。一个小剧场还用于[[角斗士|角斗士]]比赛。虽然最初的广场建筑群并非建于罗马时期，但是主要是在公元2世纪重建。<ref name="A Companion 1"/> 广场和剧院至少使用到6世纪。<ref name="From Early Roman">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=o8f_f04haw8C&pg=PA169&dq=thessaloniki+archaeology&hl=en&ei=ZFjdTt-LKIPIsgbQppWMBA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CDYQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=forum&f=false|title=From Roman to early Christian Thessalonikē: studies in religion and archaeology|author1=Laura Salah Nasrallah|author2=Charalambos Bakirtzis|author3=Steven J. Friesen|year=2010|publisher=Harvard College|accessdate=2011-12-05|archive-date=2017-02-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170214192129/https://books.google.com/books?id=o8f_f04haw8C&pg=PA169&dq=thessaloniki+archaeology&hl=en&ei=ZFjdTt-LKIPIsgbQppWMBA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CDYQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=forum&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>

